
Here’s a **streamlined, store-ready shopping list** with **standardized quantities** and **bulk-friendly packaging** (e.g., 1 cup, 1 lb, 1 jar, etc.) for easier grocery shopping. I’ve grouped items by category, adjusted for typical store sizes, and removed redundancies.

---

### **Proteins & Meat**  
- **Chicken breast**: 1 lb (cut into 1-inch cubes)  
- **Salmon fillet**: 1.25 lbs (cut into 4 portions)  
- **Shrimp**: 1 lb (peeled, with tails removed, patted dry)  
- **Eggs**: 6 large (fried, scrambled, or poached, optional)  
- **Grilled chicken breasts**: 2 medium (diced into bite-sized pieces, optional)  

---

### **Vegetables**  
- **Carrots**: 3 medium (peeled, chopped) + ½ cup (sliced)  
- **Bell peppers**: 2 red/orange/yellow (diced, halved, seeded)  
- **Broccoli**: 2 cups florets + ½ cup chopped (fresh)  
- **Cucumbers**: 4 Persian (or 1 English, diced) + 2 English (thinly sliced)  
- **Onions**: 1 medium yellow (diced) + ½ large red (thinly sliced) + ½ cup (diced)  
- **Zucchini**: 1 medium (halved lengthwise)  
- **Tomatoes**: 1 can (28 oz, diced, lightly drained) + 1 cup (fresh, diced)  
- **Mushrooms**: ½ cup (diced, fresh)  
- **Spinach**: 1 cup (fresh, chopped) + 4 cups (chopped, about 4 oz)  
- **Romaine lettuce**: 4 cups (chopped, about 1 large heart)  
- **Cabbage or kale**: 1 bunch (chopped, for coleslaw or salads)  

---

### **Dairy & Alternatives**  
- **Greek yogurt**: 3/4 cup (plain, low-fat)  
- **Cheese**: 12 slices (Cooper Sharp American) + 3/4 cup feta (crumbled)  
- **Butter**: ½ stick (softened)  
- **Plant-based milk**: ½ cup (oat milk, optional)  
- **Milk**: ¼ cup (1% milk, optional)  

---

### **Grains & Cereals**  
- **Quinoa**: ½ cup (uncooked, rinsed) + 1 cup (cooked, for salads)  
- **Pasta**: 12 oz (whole-wheat linguine, optional)  
- **Oats**: ½ cup (rolled, for granola or porridge)  
- **Pasta noodles**: 12 oz (whole-wheat, optional)  

---

### **Fruits & Sweeteners**  
- **Berries**: 3/4 cup (fresh, mixed) + 1 cup raspberries (optional)  
- **Strawberries**: 8 oz (hulled, quartered)  
- **Avocados**: 2 ripe (diced, divided)  
- **Bananas**: 2 medium  
- **Maple syrup or agave nectar**: 1 tbsp (for dressings or sweeteners)  
- **Cranberries**: ½ cup (dried, optional)  

---

### **Spices & Herbs**  
- **Salt**: 1 tsp (divided) + ¼ tsp (kosher, optional)  
- **Black pepper**: 1 tsp (freshly ground, optional) + ½ tsp (crushed red pepper flakes)  
- **Cumin**: 2 tsp  
- **Curry powder**: 1 tsp  
- **Oregano**: 1 tsp (dried) + 1/4 tsp (fresh, optional)  
- **Thyme**: ½ tsp (dried)  
- **Dill**: 2 tbsp (chopped, optional)  
- **Basil**: ½ cup (fresh, chopped) + ¼ cup (chopped, for dressings)  
- **Parsley**: ¼ cup (chopped, optional)  

---

### **Condiments & Oils**  
- **Olive oil**: 1 cup (extra virgin, for dressings)  
- **Coconut milk**: 1 cup (or half & half/cream, optional)  
- **Vinegar**:  
  - ¼ cup white wine vinegar  
  - 1 tbsp white wine vinegar (for dressings)  
  - ½ cup red wine vinegar (for marinades)  
- **Mustard**: 2 tbsp (Dijon, optional)  
- **Lemon juice**: ½ cup (freshly squeezed) + 1 tbsp (for dressings)  
- **Lime juice**: ½ of 1 medium lime (for dressings)  
- **Apple cider vinegar**: 1 tbsp (for dressings)  
- **Sesame oil**: 1 tbsp (toasted, optional)  
- **Cooking spray**: 1 tbsp (butter-flavored, optional)  

---

### **Canned & Packaged Goods**  
- **Chickpeas**: 1 can (15.5 oz, drained and rinsed)  
- **Tomatoes**: 1 can (28 oz, San Marzano, peeled, optional)  
- **Veggie broth**: 4 cups (or 1 cup, optional)  
- **Chili or tomato sauce** (optional, based on recipe needs)  
- **Canned beans**: 1 can (optional, for salads or stews)  

---

### **Optional Add-Ins**  
- **Chopped chives or parsley** (for garnish)  
- **Parmesan cheese** (for toppings)  
- **Pumpkin seeds** (for salads or snacks)  
- **Feta cheese crumbles** (for salads)  
- **Flax egg** (for vegan recipes)  
- **Quinoa or couscous** (for grain bowls)  

---
